\begin_layout Standard
Section - the Sleeping Man
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section was primarily written in order to introduce us to the hub,
 the centron, and so on.
 Amonas' mind-bomb came as an afterthought and is indeed a hurried device.
 No mechanism is evident by which it works.
 Suffice it to say that there's something permeating the hub that is not
 evident (could be neutrinnos, for all I know too).
 So, leaving that aside, we don't get much insight into the centron, other
 than perhaps it is not as it was originally, and there seem to be many
 different generations or even civilizations of people that had lived there
 at some point..
 It does not look like a normal city, but rather like an installation.
 Overall, I think I don't delve as much into it as I should.
 Rather I focus on their thoughts, which at this point seem strange.
 I mean, they still don't know where they are, but they've been through
 beams and fireballs and shit, and they still take it in their stride.
 I tried to offset that by making them ficus on the task at hand, returning,
 finding their way out, learning where they are and so on, but I seem to
 have messed this up.
 Also, apart from the zombification of Amonas, I introduce Ron, the AI,
 which I find a bit too much, a humorous note that I wanted to add for a
 bit of color, but I don't know whether or not the timing was right.
 Anyway, I think the description of Ron is a bit dull and vague, and the
 large shaft was supposed to be a large launch tube or something similar
 but as it is now I've used it remotely like a parking lot for spaceships.
 Even so, the section does what it's supposed to do, only it leaves me with
 a sense of being half-finished.
 I've got better, but I've got worse as well.
\end_layout

